In a speech at the White House, Vice President Mike Pence addressed representatives from freedom-loving nations across the Western Hemisphere at the 48th General Assembly of the Organization of American States (OAS). He expressed condolences for the victims of the volcanic eruption in Guatemala and called for an end to violence in Nicaragua. Pence also criticized the government of Nicolas Maduro in Venezuela, calling the recent election a "sham" and urging the OAS to suspend Venezuela's membership. He announced that he will be traveling to Brazil and Ecuador to strengthen security and economic relationships and bring attention to the crisis in Venezuela. Pence emphasized that the United States will continue to stand with nations that value freedom and work towards a hemisphere of freedom.